{
  "texts": [
    "The Q-test is a statistical tool used to determine whether there are significant differences in the results of each study in a meta-analysis.",
    "If p > 0.1, we usually consider the results across different studies to be similar, and a fixedeffects model can be chosen for the meta-analysis.",
    "However, if p ≤ 0.1, this suggests 1 3",
    "that there are significant differences between the studies, or heterogeneity, in which case a random-effects model should be used for the meta-analysis (Zhang & Hu, 2019).On the other hand, the I 2 statistic is used to assess the relative size of heterogeneity.",
    "Its value ranges from 0 to 100%, with larger values indicating greater heterogeneity."
  ]
}